The paper deals with the development of a control framework for underactuated flying humanoid robots, which involves the use of technologies and methods developed for Whole-Body Control and Aerial Manipulation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the control objective of asymptotic stabilization of the robot centroidal momentum, which involves the use of stability and convergence analysis techniques. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also involves simulations carried out on a model of the humanoid robot iCub, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
